  "title": "URGENT: Test Technician/Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Set up, calibrate, test, and troubleshoot circuits, components, instruments, and mechanical assemblies</li><li>Develop or follow test specifications, methods, and procedures based on drawings and diagrams</li><li>Test assemblies and final systems; perform rework as needed</li><li>Prepare technical reports detailing findings and recommended solutions</li><li>Assist in selecting and setting up specialized test equipment</li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Nitec / Diploma in Engineering</li><li>Ability to read technical drawings and operate precision testing instruments</li><li>Hands-on experience with semiconductor equipment; optics alignment experience a plus</li><li>Strong troubleshooting, analytical, and data analysis skills</li><li>Excellent communication, teamwork, and interpersonal skills</li><li>Comfortable working in shifts and cleanroom environments</li></ul><p><br />Interested applicants, please click on <strong>“Apply Now”</strong> or submit your resume to <a href=\"mailto:ref68@trustrecruit.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>ref68@trustrecruit.com.sg</strong></a></p><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>Important Note: Trust Recruit Pte Ltd is committed to safeguarding your personal data in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA).</p><p>Please read our privacy statement on our corporate website <a href=\"http://www.trustrecruit.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">www.trustrecruit.com.sg</a></p><p>Trust Recruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 19C9950</p><p>EA Personnel: John Angeline</p><p>EA Personnel Reg No: R1544851</p>",
